		 Third party services 
		  
			Of course we are all for responsible disclosure, which you might have seen if you have read our blog. So here we have listed all the third party services we use in different ways in alphabetical order and an added a short comment on why or how we use them.

		 Adyen 
		 
			For payments we use Adyen. You can read their   ="http://www.adyen.com/downloads/contract/AdyenTermsandConditions.pdf">terms and conditions  on their website. 
		 
	 
	 class="small"   class="main-text-cont">
		 Amazon 
		 We use various Amazon services in Ireland, including Amazon EC2, Amazon RDS, Amazon SES and Amazon S3 to provide Detectify to you.

			Whenever you have a question for us. We will receive that question and answer it via desk. You find their   ="http://www.desk.com/privacy">privacy policy here  and their   ="http://www.desk.com/terms">terms of use here .

			/**  
			* Encode/decode Internationalized Domain Names.  
			*   
			* The class allows to convert internationalized domain names  
			* (see RFC 3490 for details) as they can be used with various registries worldwide  
			* to be translated between their original (localized) form and their encoded form  
			* as it will be used in the DNS (Domain Name System).  
			*  
			* The class provides two public methods, encode() and decode(), which do exactly  
			* what you would expect them to do. You are allowed to use complete domain names,  
			* simple strings and complete email addresses as well. That means, that you might  
			* use any of the following notations:  
			*   
			* - www.nörgler.com  
			* - xn--nrgler-wxa  
			* - xn--brse-5qa.xn--knrz-1ra.info  
			*  
			* Unicode input might be given as either UTF-8 string, UCS-4 string or UCS-4 array.  
			* Unicode output is available in the same formats.  
			* You can select your preferred format via {@link set_paramter()}.  
			*  
			* ACE input and output is always expected to be ASCII.  
			*

	$(document).ready(function() {
		//Hide/display grid
		gridShowing = false;
		$(window).on('keypress', function(e){
			if(e.shiftKey && e.ctrlKey && (e.charCode === 1 || e.charCode === 65)) {
				$('#grid').toggleClass('hidden');
				gridShowing = true;
			}
			if(gridShowing && e.charCode === 0) {
				$('#grid').addClass('hidden');
				gridShowing = false;
			}
		});
		$('html').addClass('local');
		//$('#grid').show();

	});
